## Is Sapphire Durable Enough for Daily Wear?

Yes. Sapphire (corundum) is 9 on the Mohs hardness scale — second only to diamond (10). It's harder than ruby, harder than emerald, harder than tanzanite. Sapphire is one of the best choices for a ring worn every day.

**Comparison:**
| Stone | Mohs Hardness | Daily Wear |
|---|---|---|
| Diamond | 10 | Excellent |
| **Sapphire** | **9** | **Excellent** |
| Ruby | 9 | Excellent |
| Emerald | 7.5–8 | Good (more brittle) |
| Tanzanite | 6–7 | Moderate (prone to scratching) |
| Opal | 5.5–6.5 | Poor for daily wear |

Sapphire engagement rings and everyday rings are an excellent choice. A sapphire will not scratch easily, does not chip readily, and holds up well to the knocks of daily life. It's why royals chose it for a ring meant to last generations.

