## FAQ: Blue Nile Sapphire Rings

**Are Blue Nile sapphires real or fake?**
Real — natural sapphires, earth-mined. Blue Nile does not sell synthetic (lab-created) sapphires in their ring catalog as of {{month_year}}.

**Are the sapphires heat-treated?**
Almost certainly, yes. Over 95% of commercial sapphires are heat-treated to improve color. This is permanent, stable, and universally accepted. Blue Nile doesn't certify each sapphire individually at this price point, so assume heat treatment.

**Can I use a Blue Nile sapphire ring as an engagement ring?**
Yes. Sapphire is Mohs 9 (hardness), making it an excellent choice for daily wear. The oval sapphire halo style is one of the most popular engagement ring alternatives to diamonds.

**Is the Riviera Pavé Sapphire Eternity resizable?**
No — it's a full eternity ring with stones all the way around. Order your exact size. Blue Nile offers free size exchanges within 30 days.

**What's the difference between the 250th Anniversary Collection and regular pieces?**
The 250th Anniversary Collection pieces are specific Blue Nile-designed rings, often with slightly more elaborate settings than standard catalog pieces. They're priced comparably and available with the same return policy.

**Which is better for everyday wear — blue or pink sapphire?**
Both are equally durable (Mohs 9). The choice is purely aesthetic. Blue is more traditional/formal; pink is warmer/more romantic.

**Do Blue Nile sapphire rings come with a certificate?**
No gemological certificate for the sapphire (standard for colored stones at this price point). The metal is stamped with the correct hallmarks (14K, 18K, or Pt for platinum).

**Is the James Allen clearance real?**
Yes. The JA.com website is shutting down (Signet Jewelers announced this in their fiscal year report). The inventory transferred to Blue Nile and is being cleared at 30–60% discounts. These are legitimate price reductions, not inflated "before" prices.

**Can I get a sapphire ring engraved?**
Free engraving is available on select styles at checkout. Band-style rings (like the eternity ring) and rings with flat interior surfaces can be engraved. Preset cocktail rings typically cannot.

**How do I choose between 7x5mm and 8x6mm sapphire sizes?**
A 7x5mm oval is approximately 1.0–1.5ct equivalent visual size — elegant and proportionate for most hands. An 8x6mm is approximately 2.0–2.5ct equivalent — noticeably larger, more statement-oriented. If you're unsure, the 8x6mm Oval Sapphire Halo at $3,318 (23 reviews, 30% off) is the safer crowd-validated choice.

**What metal is best for blue sapphire?**
White gold or platinum. The cool metal amplifies the blue of the stone. Yellow gold can work with certain warm-toned sapphires but is less traditional for blue. For pink sapphire, rose gold is the natural pairing.

**Does Blue Nile offer sapphire engagement ring customization?**
No — preset only. If you want to select your own sapphire and set it in a custom setting, you need a custom jeweler. Blue Nile's sapphire catalog is preset rings only.

